ong top contenders |work=Gold Derby |first1=Chris |last1=Beachum |first2=Daniel |last2=Montgomery |first3=Marcus |last3=James Dixon |date=July 26, 2017 |accessdate=October 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite New Comedy Series\n| data-sort-value=\"Good Place, The\" | ''The Good Place''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://peopleschoice.com/2017/01/18/peoples-choice-awards-2017-winners/ |title=People's Choice Awards 2017: Full List Of Winners |work=People's Choice |first=Nuzhat |last=Naoreen |date=January 18, 2017 |accessdate=October 11, 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211144521/http://peopleschoice.com/2017/01/18/peoples-choice-awards-2017-winners/ |archivedate=February 11, 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[43rd Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Fantasy Television Series|Best Fantasy Television Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Good Place, The\" | ''The Good Place''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/awards/saturn-awards-nominations-2017-rogue-one-walking-dead-1202000833/ |title=Saturn Awards Nominations 2017: 'Rogue One,' 'Walking Dead' Lead |last=McNary |first=Dave |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=March 2, 2017 |accessdate=March 2, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[33rd TCA Awards|TCA Awards]]\n| Individual Achievement in Comedy\n| data-sort-value=\"Bell, Kristen\" |[[Kristen Bell]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/atlanta-this-is-us-handmaids-tale-tca-awards-1202470253/ |title='Atlanta,' 'This Is Us,' 'Handmaid's Tale' Lead TCA Awards Nominations |work=Variety |first=Joe |last=Otterson |date=June 19, 2017 |accessdate=October 11, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Comedy\n| data-sort-value=\"Good Place, The\" | ''The Good Place''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| Outstanding New Program\n| data-sort-value=\"Good Place, The\" |''The Good Place''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"12\" |2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[8th Critics' Choice Television Awards|Critics' Choice Television Awards]]\n|[[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actor in a Comedy Series|Best Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Danson, Ted\" | Ted Danson\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2018/01/11/critics-choice-awards-winners-television-2018-full-list/ |title=Critics' Choice Awards: Big Little Lies, Sterling K. Brown and More TV Winners |work=TVLine |first=Andy |last=Swift |date=January 11, 2018 |accessdate=January 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actress in a Comedy Series|Best Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Bell, Kristen\" | Kristen Bell\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Hugo Award]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Hugo Award for Best Dramatic Presentation|Best Dramatic Presentation, Short Form]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Michael's Gambit\" | \"Michael's Gambit\", written and directed by [[Michael Schur]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=\"Hugo-2018\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/8/20/17698208/2018-hugo-awards-n-k-jemisin-martha-wells-science-fiction-fantasy-books |title=Here are the winners of the 2018 Hugo Awards |publisher=The Verge |first=Andrew |last=Liptak |date=August 20, 2018 |accessdate=August 20, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Trolley Problem, The\" | \"The Trolley Problem\", written by Josh Siegal & Dylan Morgan and directed by Dean Holland\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=Hugo-2018/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[44th People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Awards]]\n| Best Comedy Show\n| data-sort-value=\"Good Place, The\" | ''The Good Place''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/shows/peoples_choice_awards/news/963752/2018-people-s-choice-awards-complete-list-of-no